Repost: @choralchameleon **Meet George Burton, Choral Chameleon's 2023-2024 Artist in Residence**

COMPOSER AND MULTI-INSTRUMENTALIST GEORGE BURTON IS NAMED CHORAL CHAMELEON'S 7TH COMPOSER-IN-RESIDENCE

Award-winning pianist, composer and bandleader George Burton has been called a lot of things— “formidable” (NPR),“charismatic” (The New York Times), “revolutionary” (Nextbop), “soulful” (Philadelphia Inquirer); his music “multidimensional” (Phila. Inq.), “sublime” (NPR). Burton will compose two new works for Choral Chameleon during the 2023-2024 concert season and will serve as a guest faculty member in Composition during the June 2024 Institute for Composers. Welcome to the Choral Chameleon family, George! We're so excited to have you with us!

Follow George here: @daporge

Repost: @operaprojectcolumbus We are incredibly fortunate at OPC to work with some of the most talented pianists that exist.  This week we celebrate pianists with World Pianist Day, and we would like to introduce you to George Burton, who will be joining us for our limited engagement performance, November, 28.  We are elated to bring his talent to our Columbus audience. 

Award-nominated pianist, composer and bandleader George Burton has been called a lot of things— “formidable” (NPR),“charismatic” (The New York Times), “revolutionary” (Nextbop), “soulful” (Philadelphia Inquirer); his music “multidimensional” (Phila. Inq.), “sublime” (NPR). 

There is a dynamic quality to hearing Burton play in that just when you think you've spotted an influence or are ready to compare him to one of the greats, he takes a turn, blending modern and classical in a way that is both playful and transcendent. The vitality in Burton’s music is apparent in his effortless switch in tempo, each note carefully thought out, lingering, distinct and alive. He finds balance where others would waver, bringing the fullest expression of himself to the music he creates.

“George Burton represents what many of jazz’s most exciting figures hoped the genre would become: precarious, dynamic, revolutionary ... unable to be contained.” — NEXTBOP

Join us for conversation, dinner and a performance.

I've always had strong connections with the artists I collaborate with. The individual behind The Yule Log's cover art is practically family now and has been for the better part of a decade. Throughout this period, I've held a deep appreciation for the work of @jackrichardson_illustration.

When I shared my project idea and vision with him, he immediately captured it perfectly. This artwork graces the album's back cover. 

The is the depiction of @aryssaleighburrs who was a special guest on the track Jesu Parvule.
